[SN]TITLE[SN]
Missing Glasgow pensioner traced

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pensioner with dementia who went missing from his Glasgow home has been traced.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Patrick Hart, 82, had last been seen at his home in Saracen Street, Possilpark, at about 16:00 on Monday.
Police carried out searches involving police dogs and a helicopter and appealed for people to check private CCTV footage.
A spokeswoman confirmed that Mr Hart had been found on Tuesday and thanked the public for their help to find him.
